{
  "texts": [
    "While some would call for a centralised Ground Truth repository, this could be a costly affair, and result in double the work, as funding agencies can have requirements to store the output in available.",
    "specified (e.g.",
    "national) repositories.",
    "6 Consequently, a solution to this problem of the decentralised distribution of sources is discussed below.",
    "Generally, storing data in a FAIR-compliant, noncommercial repository with a persistent identifier, like Digital Object Identifiers (DOIs), is preferred."
  ]
}